The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of sparse binary matrices and sublinear-time recovery techniques suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
